The paper discusses a practical approach for answering questions related to auditing and debugging data and queries, which falls under the domain of databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a graph-based provenance model that supports reverse reasoning, which is a common technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the implementation of a system called PUG, which involves data structures and algorithms commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
